title: Cloud Pub/Sub Message v1
name: MessagePublishedData
description: A message that is published by publishers and consumed by subscribers.

PubsubMessage.description: A message published to a topic.

data.description: The message data field. If this field is empty, the message must contain at least one attribute. A base64-encoded string.

attributes.description: Attributes for this message. If this field is empty, the message must contain non-empty data. This can be used to filter messages on the subscription.

messageId.description: ID of this message, assigned by the server when the message is published. Guaranteed to be unique within the topic. This value may be read by a subscriber that receives a PubsubMessage via a subscriptions.pull call or a push delivery. It must not be populated by the publisher in a topics.publish call.

subscription.description: The resource name of the subscription for which this event was generated. The format of the value is `projects/{project-id}/subscriptions/{subscription-id}`.
